> **Note:** To reach 90+, additionally implement: async DB driver, frontend testing, E2E tests, APM integration, and staging environment.

## Deployment Checklist

- [ ] Rotate `SECRET_KEY` — generate new 64-byte key
- [ ] Remove `.env` from git history (`git filter-branch` or BFG)
- [ ] Verify all `_init_.py` → `__init__.py` renames
- [ ] Confirm no endpoints are unauthenticated (except `/health`, public pages)
- [ ] Set `ENVIRONMENT=production` and `DEBUG=false`
- [ ] Configure PostgreSQL with strong password
- [ ] Enable Redis AUTH
- [ ] Configure reverse proxy (nginx/Caddy) with SSL termination
- [ ] Set `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` to production domain only
- [ ] Run full test suite: `pytest tests/ -v --cov`
- [ ] Build production Docker image: `docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build`
- [ ] Verify health endpoint: `curl http://localhost:8000/health`
- [ ] Configure log drain (CloudWatch, Datadog, or ELK)
- [ ] Set up monitoring alerts for 5xx errors and latency
- [ ] Schedule DB backups (pg_dump cron)
- [ ] Document incident response runbook
